    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-02-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="514"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/2–749</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Executive Secretary of the National Security
                        Council</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Souers</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-08">February 8,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Current Position of the United States Respecting
                    Delivery of Aid to China</p>
                <p>After discussion with key members of Congress of the advisability of suspending
                    further shipments of military aid to China as recommended <pb facs="0497"
                        n="487" xml:id="pg_487"/> by the National Security Council in the reference
                        action,<note n="43" xml:id="d514fn43">NSC Action No. 180, February 3; see
                        editorial notes, <ref target="#pg_482">p. 482</ref>.</note> the President
                    has decided that, in order not to discourage continued Chinese resistance to
                    communist aggression, such shipments of military aid should not be suspended nor
                    terminated but no effort should be made to expedite deliveries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sidney</hi> W. <hi rend="smallcaps">Souers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
